description.narrative: UNICEF data on COVID-19 pandemic estimates ten million additional child marriages may occur before 2030. UNFPA estimates there may be as many as 2 million cases of female genital mutilation by 2030 that could have been averted. UNICEF promoted evidence-, rights- and participation-based intervention approaches for improving policy frameworks for prevention and elimination of harmful practices, including child marriage and FGM, improving access to gender-responsive girl friendly services, and generating/utilizing data and evidence. UNICEF built the capacity of national actors and rolled out toolkits to support programming towards shifting discriminatory social and gender norms in humanitarian/development context. | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/03/2022
